The paper deals with finding a maximal independent set in a graph in a distributed setting, which is a fundamental problem in distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves analyzing the complexity of the algorithm, which suggests it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.AL (Computational Complexity). The paper mentions the use of random ordering of nodes, which could indicate it belongs to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the history-independence property, which could suggest it belongs to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
